detailed-description.p:
A first example relates to a method for determining the vision disorder of an eye of a spectacle wearer, comprising:





providing measurement values from a first and a second measurement of the vision disorder of the eye of the spectacle wearer;

calculating an estimator or estimated value for the vision disorder of the eye of the spectacle wearer based on the measurement values from the first and the second measurement, wherein measurement inaccuracies or measurement deviations of the first and the second measurements of the vision disorder are taken into account in the calculation of the estimated value of the vision disorder.

An exemplary method for determining the vision disorder of a spectacle wearer comprises the following steps:





1) matching of the subjective and/or objective refractions in order to eliminate systematic differences in the two measurement methods;

2) combination of the refractions thus matched to one another by forming a weighted average.

